## 8. Authentication Flow

### Register Flow
1. User fills register form (name, email, password, password confirmation, state)
2. Role defaults to `viewer` — only `super_admin` can promote roles later
3. Laravel Breeze handles hashing + session
4. On success → redirect to `/dashboard`
5. Activity logged: "New user registered"

### Login Flow
1. User fills login form (email, password)
2. Laravel `Auth::attempt()` checks credentials
3. On success → redirect to `/dashboard`
4. On failure → back with error message (do not reveal if email exists)

### Forgot Password Flow
1. User enters email on `/forgot-password`
2. Laravel sends reset link via email (uses `MAIL_*` env vars)
3. User clicks link → `/reset-password/{token}`
4. User sets new password → redirected to login

### Role Middleware
```
Route::middleware(['auth', 'role:super_admin'])->group(...)
Route::middleware(['auth', 'role:super_admin,state_officer'])->group(...)
Route::middleware(['auth'])->group(...)
```
`CheckRole` middleware reads `$request->user()->role` and aborts with 403 if mismatch.

